InsurancePolicy 1 -- * Transaction
A Transaction has An InsurancePolicy. It must always have exactly, one, and can never have none. And there is an upper bound of at most one InsurancePolicy.
An InsurancePolicy has some Transactions. It can have none, and there is no upper bound defined.
When a Transaction is created, its InsurancePolicy must be assigned. When a Transaction is deleted, its InsurancePolicy is not deleted and its list of Transactions is decreased. When an InsurancePolicy is deleted, its Transactions are not deleted. They are assigned to another InsurancePolicy.

InsuredProperty 1 -- 1 PropertyInsurancePolicy
A PropertyInsurancePolicy has An InsuredProperty. It must always have exactly, one, and can never have none. And there is an upper bound of at most one InsuredProperty.
An InsuredProperty has A PropertyInsurancePolicy. It must always have exactly, one, and can never have none. And there is an upper bound of at most one PropertyInsurancePolicy.
There must always be an equal number of PropertyInsurancePolicy and InsuredProperty, connected as Pairs. When an InsuredProperty is created, its PropertyInsurancePolicy must be created at the same time. When an InsuredProperty is deleted, its PropertyInsurancePolicy is deleted at the same time.
